THE CELLAR - - 125s 226e Market & 3rd Street

The Cellar is the Compound's most popular nightspot, and it isn’t hard to see why. With its Euro-tech ambiance and secluded location, it is the preferred hangout for an incredibly mixed crowd.

Patrons can listen to live music using the Real Audio jukebox. Constantly changing, live music with over 1,000 different channels and 100,000 songs provided by Spinner.com. The club channel is usually "Industrial", but you can pick what you like (just don’t let the bartender catch you listening to "Country").

-

By far the most unique feature of the Cellar is its working dancefloor. Just step on to the flashing floor and get swept into the dance. Use your third-person view and gestures to make sure you don't look like a dork.

Before you leave, make sure you check out the bathroom walls. Everything you read has been added by other patrons. If you have any words of wisdom to add, just contact the owner. (use any GBC phonebooth or telegram Rhedd)
